main event: The report describes a sighting of an unidentified object in the sky, including details about its appearance, motion, and behavior.
interesting points: The object was described as a bright, whitish-blue, round object that was quiet and moved in an erratic pattern, including appearing to stand still, suddenly speeding up and slowing down, and changing brightness.
The witness estimated the object was approximately 30 feet in diameter and flew at an altitude of about the height of the trees.
The object was observed for around 30 minutes, with the witness shining a light at it at one point and the object then returning in the same direction before crossing over.
The witness was unable to get a photograph as their camera shutter jammed.
The witness estimated the object's speed to be around 3,900 miles per hour.
